    "discriminators": [
     "The shortest, driest impulse in MECHANICAL: a single bright click of a few tens of milliseconds with essentially no ring. Very high crest factor, near-zero sustain, front-loaded envelope.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-SWITCH: UCS itself admits the overlap. A switch tends to be a heavier two-part event - a throw and a detent, so transient_count near 2 - with more low-mid body; a click is one small bright event. Signal narrows the pair, text must settle it.",
     "Against CLOCKS-TICK: the same impulse, but REPEATED periodically. If onset_periodicity is high and the train runs for seconds, it is a clock, not a click.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-RATCHET: a ratchet is a dense burst of many clicks, not one."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "MECHSwtch",
