    "discriminators": [
     "Meshing cogs: a CONTINUOUS bed, not discrete events. The tooth-passing frequency lays a strong tonal comb over a grinding broadband floor, so gears read as sustained and stationary, with a high onset_periodicity but a far higher onset_rate than a ratchet.",
     "Grinding gears push spectral_flux and inharmonicity up; a clean gearbox stays tonal and steady.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-RATCHET: a ratchet is silent between clicks (low sustain_ratio); gears never go silent.",
     "Small clock gears go to CLOCKS-MECHANICS - a size judgement, though size does show up as low_band_energy."
    ],
