    "discriminators": [
     "Pressurized gas or fluid through a restriction: a broadband HISS with a decaying pressure tail, usually bracketed by a valve click and a cylinder thunk. Very high spectral_flatness with very low harmonicity and a high centroid - a noise source, not an impact and not a tone.",
     "Hydraulic rams add a low groan under the hiss; a pneumatic damper on a self-closing door is pure hiss with a long release.",
     "Against AIR-HISS: acoustically the SAME sound. What makes it MECHANICAL is the machine around it - the valve click, the ram thunk. Text decides.",
