    "discriminators": [
     "A briefcase or luggage latch: a spring-loaded metallic snap - bright, sharp, slightly RINGING (metal, so inharmonic partials and a real decay tail rather than the dead thock of a plastic click), often a two-part release-then-open or close-then-catch.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-LOCK: a lock has a key and tumbler stage - a rasping multi-click sequence before the bolt throws. A latch is just the snap.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-CLICK: brighter metallic ring and a longer decay.",
     "Door hardware belongs to DOORS-HARDWARE; this is cases, luggage, toolboxes, gates."
    ],
